Creighton and Gregg
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33762" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole gilvescens Creighton &amp; Gregg" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole gilvescens Creighton &amp; Gregg" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilvescens">Pheidole gilvescens</taxonomicName>
Creighton and Gregg 1955: 5. First available use of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:251696" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole xerophila subsp. tucsonica var. gilvescens" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole xerophila tucsonica var. gilvescens Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="577" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="xerophila" subSpecies="tucsonica" variety="gilvescens">Pheidole xerophila subsp. tucsonica var. gilvescens Wheeler</taxonomicName>
